cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.AI. 

This paper introduces a new database system, Opine, that models subjective data and processes queries involving subjective experiences expressed in natural language. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), which deals with the design, implementation, and management of databases. 

The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it discusses how Opine translates subjective queries against the subjective database schema. 

Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with processing queries expressed in natural language. 

Human-computer interaction (cs.HC) is also a likely sub-category as the paper aims to satisfy user needs more effectively and accurately. 

Finally, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the development of a new database system that can process subjective queries, which is a task that requires AI techniques such as natural language processing and machine learning.
